Overview
Combining the pulsating drive of Showtime's Homeland with the fascinating historical detail of such of narrative nonfiction bestsellers as Double Cross and In the Garden of Beasts, Dark Invasion is Howard BlumÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s gritty, high-energy true-life tale of German espionage and terror on American soil during World War I, and the NYPD Inspector who helped uncover the plotÃ¢â‚¬â€the basis for the film to be produced by and starring Bradley Cooper.

When a Ã¢â‚¬Å“neutralÃ¢â‚¬ï¿½ United States becomes a trading partner for the Allies early in World War I, the Germans implement a secret plan to strike back. A team of saboteursÃ¢â‚¬â€including an expert on germ warfare, a Harvard professor, and a brilliant, debonair spymasterÃ¢â‚¬â€devise a series of Ã¢â‚¬Å“mysterious accidentsÃ¢â‚¬ï¿½ using explosives and biological weapons, to bring down vital targets such as ships, factories, livestock, and even captains of industry like J. P. Morgan.

New York Police Inspector Tom Tunney, head of the departmentÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s Bomb Squad, is assigned the difficult mission of stopping them. Assembling a team of loyal operatives, the cunning Irish cop hunts for the conspirators among a population of more than eight million Germans. But the deeper he finds himself in this labyrinth of deception, the more Tunney realizes that the enemyÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s plan is far more complex and more dangerous than he suspected.

